nts,\n\n--- Cast your vote for MCS 2010 Vice Principal ---\n\nPlease cast your vote to our VP candidate <span style=\"font-size: small;\">呂宗龍  (</span>Chung-Long Lu) by this Saturday via e-mail or fill in and return the ballot to your parent representative. I\'m impressed by Chung-Long\'s introduction of himself and his willingness to devote time and effort to our school. Let\'s all give him a big hand!\n\n--- 5/8 Taiwan Traditional Culture Week ---\n\nReminder, this event is from 10am to 3pm at Novi Sheraton Hotel this Saturday. Lion dance team will perform at 10am. Invite your friends to enjoy this rare opportunity to learn traditional culture demonstrated by national experts from Taiwan.\n\n--- Exchange of unwanted items (books, toys, household items...) at parents lounge ---\n\nWe all have some surplus or used items that other families may find better use. Why not take them to our school to share with other parents this Saturday? Young families maybe interested in the used books or baby stuff that your kids has grown out of. Let\'s start the sharing this Saturday!\n\n--- Eric Wu\'s tennis class ---\n\nEric Wu conduct the first tennis class last Saturday after school at schoolcraft tennis court. There are 12 students attended the training for over an hour. Eric did teaching on basic stroke for forehand and backhand. The students are divided into experienced and beginner groups. They made good practices. The class will be held at same place and same time this weekend.\n\n--- Take a look of speech contest photos posted on MCS website ---\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>\n\n--- Hunan-Hunan will deliver your food orders this week ---\n\n如有家长想訂东西請电(313)389-0939\n\n--- parents on duty ---\n\n楊耀光\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 5/8/2010',0,'','inhe