周年的第一天,密西根僑民將於元月一日上午十一點,在美華中心廣場舉行密西根的升旗典禮(全球以美國加州時間早上八點為準),希望台灣僑民們踴躍參加,也歡迎攜帶美國當地朋友參加,升旗典禮過後,於12點籌備會將提供多種粥點,以祛寒氣,希望僑學各界能多多呼朋引友踴躍參加,也希望鼓勵年輕學子參與.\n\n時間 : 元月一日上午十一點,\n\n地點 : 美華活動中心廣場:32585 Concord Drive, Madison Hts., MI 48071\n\n有問題者可洽: 周綵玲2483208888孫絡典5868263936\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Holidays Break</span></strong>\n\nThere will be no school for 12/25/2010 and 1/1/2011, due to holidays break. We  wish your family the gifts of joy, good health and peace this  season. We wish you warm wonderful times with family and friends and  much love. We look forward to exciting and challenging new learning  experiences in the 2011 New Year!','MCS Newsletter     Dec. 18, 2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','116-revision','','','2010-12-16 18:10:06','2010-12-16 22:10:06','',116,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=117',0,'revision','',0),(118,1,'2011-01-08 00:23:08','2011-01-08 04:23:08','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Happy New Year</span></strong>\r\n\r\nI hope all of you enjoyed the holiday break and spent some relaxing time with friends and family.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Communication</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAs  we discussed at beginning of school year, we would like to promote  email communication between teachers and parents/students so that we can  save paper and protect environment. Teachers will send out weekly  teaching progress and homework assignment by email. If you don’t have  computer to access these communication, you can stop by Madonna  University library during our regular school hours and there are many  computers available.\r\n\r\nWhile  I organized our school contact directory, I noticed that several  families were not on the weekly newsletter distribution list. If you  didn\'t receive our weekly newsletters in the past, you can go to school  website for archive information.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe  had reviewed the survey result with each teacher individually on  12/18/2010. This survey served as a bridge between teachers and  parents/students and we will conduct another survey on later part of  this school year.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Pre-Register for 2<sup>nd</sup> semester </span></strong>\r\n\r\nPre-register  for next semester will begin this week (1/8) and end on (1/15). You can  save $20.00 for each student, if you pre-register. It\'s school policy  that if you do not pre-register, <strong><em>you will be charged $20.00 registration fee for each student you enroll.</em></strong><strong> </strong>Registration form is attached and also available on school website.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">New Year Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nEvent Date: Saturday, 1/29/2011\r\n\r\nTickets on sale: 1/8/2011. Adults: $10.00, Students: $5.00\r\n\r\nNew Year Party is <strong><em>one </em></strong>event includes students\' performance and dinner.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Calendars</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe  will have some 2011 calendars from Taiwan available this Saturday at  parents lounge. Limited quantity and first come first serve.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\nHunan-Hunan will be on campus this Saturday; you may place your order in advance and pick up at school.','MCS Newsletter        Jan. 8, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-jan-8-2011','','','2011-01-08 00:23:08','2011-01-08 04:23:08','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=118',0,'post','',0),(119,1,'2011-01-08 00:22:43','2011-01-08 04:22:43','','MCS Newsletter        Jan. 8, 2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','118-revision','','','2011-01-08 00:22:43','2011-01-08 04:22:43','',118,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=119',0,'revision','',0),(120,1,'2011-01-20 00:10:38','2011-01-20 04:10:38','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Kevin Wang (王惠章) picking up the bakery from QQ bakery last week.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Spring 2010-2011</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThis  weekend will be the beginning of Spring 2010-2011 semester. Welcome  those new students and families. Because New Year Party is scheduled  next week, <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">we will have after school curriculums this week for those who need more practice.</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">New Year Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nEvent Date: Saturday, 1/29/2011 at 2:30 pm\r\n\r\nTickets on sale now: Adults: $10.00, Students: $5.00\r\n\r\nNew Year Party is <strong><em>one </em></strong>event includes students\' performance and dinner.\r\n\r\nWe are highly encouraging all school members to invite friends and families to celebrate the year of rabbit.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">New Year Party Last Preparation Meeting</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe will have one more meeting for all parents rep\'s from each class and staff this week to make sure we have everything covered.\r\n\r\nLocation: Parents Lounge\r\n\r\nTime: 1:45pm','MCS Newsletter  Jan. 22, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-jan-22-2011','','','2011-01-20 00:10:38','2011-01-20 04:10:38','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=120',0,'post','',0),(121,1,'2011-01-20 00:10:05','2011-01-20 04:10:05','','MCS Newsletter  ',0,'','inherit','open','open','','120-revision','','','2011-01-20 00:10:05','2011-01-20 04:10:05','',120,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=121',0,'revision','',0),